  "prompt": "How can I use two WhatsApp accounts with the same number on different devices?",
  "response": "Using two WhatsApp accounts with the same number on different devices is generally not supported by the official WhatsApp application. WhatsApp is designed to work with one account per phone number and one device at a time. However, there are a few workarounds you can consider if you need to access your WhatsApp account on multiple devices:\n\n1. **WhatsApp Web/Desktop:**\n   - You can use WhatsApp Web or the desktop application to access your account on a computer. Simply go to the WhatsApp Web website or open the desktop app and scan the QR code with your phone's WhatsApp app to link your account. This still uses the same number and requires your phone to be connected to the internet.\n\n2. **WhatsApp on Multiple Phones (Not Officially Supported):**\n   - As of my last update, there is no official way to use the same WhatsApp number on two different phones simultaneously. You can only switch devices by registering your number on the second device, which will log you out of the first device.\n\n3. **Linked Devices Feature:**\n   - WhatsApp has been gradually rolling out a multi-device feature. This allows you to use linked devices without needing your phone to be constantly connected. You can connect up to four devices, such as computers or tablets. However, this does not support linking the same WhatsApp account to another smartphone directly.\n\nAlways verify the latest updates from WhatsApp's official communications, as features may have changed since my last update. Be cautious of third-party applications or services that claim to offer this functionality, as they may violate WhatsApp's terms of service or jeopardize your account's security.",
